FBIS4-26580 "drchi121_n_94004" FBIS-CHI-94-121 Daily Report 21 Jun 1994 Economic & Agricultural Price Controls Continued on Certain Commodities Price Controls Continued on Certain Commodities HK2306023294 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE in Chinese 1041 GMT 21 Jun 94 HK2306023294 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE Chinese BFN [Text] Beijing, 21 Jun (ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE) -- While gradually removing price controls where appropriate over the next few years, China will continue to exercise direct state control over the prices of five types of commodities and services. The five types of commodities and services are: Less competitive commodities that have a great bearing on social stability and on the long-term development of the national economy, such as crude oil, natural gas, and a few rare metals; Commodities whose prices are strictly controlled by the government including some medicines and weapons; Living quarters offered to civil servants and low-income earners; Utilities where competition is inappropriate, such as public transport, urban water and gas supplies, electricity for general and production purposes, rail passenger and freight transport, the mail service, and telecommunications; Major facilities and services such as various types of social public insurance, public education, and health care.
